    thinking: "**Designing the Dashboard Layout**\n\nI\'m now diving into `App.tsx` and considering the overall page design. My focus is on creating a Lusion-style aesthetic for the side controller panel, titles, and explanatory text. I\'m aiming for a premium software laboratory dashboard feel with an immersive, beautiful layout.\n\n\n**Defining the UI Elements**\n\nI\'ve decided on an absolute pitch-black background with the hex code `#030305`. The primary control panel will be a floating sidebar with a crisp, transparent glass blur effect, utilizing `backdrop-blur-md bg-opacity-40 bg-zinc-950 border border-zinc-800`. I\'m going with \"Inter\" for the general typography and \"JetBrains Mono\" for data elements to achieve a minimalist, premium look. I\'ve also outlined the presets I would like, and have identified the slider variables!\n\n\n**Refining the Parameter Controls**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the control parameters. I\'ve defined ranges for alignment snap speed, particle size scale, interactive mouse warp radius, and mouse repel force. The plan is to allow adjustments to these variables for a highly customizable user experience.\n\n\\n\\n\nI\'m now deciding on a few curated color presets, based on amber and gold. I\'m thinking of \"Classic Amber,\" \"Solar Flare,\" \"Champagne Gold,\" and \"Neon Luminous\" options for visual variety. I\'m also planning a dynamic reshuffle button that causes an explosive blast and reset!\n\n\n**Displaying Key Metrics**\n\nI\'m now integrating a live statistics panel in `App.tsx` using Tailwind. My current focus is showing particle counts (which I\'ll set to 524,288), draw calls (under 20), and the simulation state. I\'m verifying the initial `App.tsx` structure and configuration for the React setup, making sure `lucide-react` is correctly installed, and planning to use its icons (Sparkles, Sliders, Eye, RefreshCw, etc.) within the layout, following proper import practices.\n\n\n"
